2. Overall Description
2.1 Product Perspective

The E-Book Management System is a web-based application developed to provide a centralized platform for managing and accessing digital books. The system is designed to overcome the limitations of traditional book management methods, such as physical storage constraints, inefficient searching, and difficulty in maintaining large collections of resources.
This platform enables users to access e-books remotely, reducing dependency on physical libraries and improving accessibility. The system also provides administrative capabilities for managing digital content, maintaining metadata, and controlling user access.
The E-Book Management System functions as a self-contained application that focuses on improving efficiency, organization, and security in digital resource management while supporting modern educational needs.
2.2 Product Functions
The major functions of the E-Book Management System include:
Allowing users to register and log in securely.
Enabling users to search for e-books using categories, authors, or keywords.
Providing users with the ability to view book details and access digital content.
Allowing administrators to upload, update, categorize, and delete e-books.
Maintaining an organized repository for efficient storage and retrieval of books.
Implementing authentication and access control to ensure data security.
Monitoring system activities to support smooth and organized operations.
These functions collectively enhance accessibility, simplify book management, and improve user experience.
2.3 User Characteristics
The system is designed for two primary types of users:
Administrator
Administrators are responsible for managing the overall system. They possess basic technical knowledge and are authorized to maintain the digital library. Their responsibilities include uploading e-books, managing metadata, controlling user access, and monitoring system performance.
Users
Users include students, educators, and individuals seeking digital learning resources. They are expected to have basic computer knowledge and the ability to navigate web applications. Users interact with the system to search, browse, and access e-books conveniently.
The system interface is designed to be simple and user-friendly to accommodate users with varying levels of technical expertise.
2.4 Constraints
The development and operation of the E-Book Management System are subject to the following constraints:
The system depends on internet connectivity for remote access.
Performance may be influenced by server capacity and storage availability.
Strong security measures must be implemented to prevent unauthorized access and protect digital content.
The system should comply with standard software engineering practices to ensure reliability and maintainability.
Access to copyrighted material must be managed responsibly to avoid legal issues.
These constraints are considered to ensure the system operates efficiently and securely.
